  "slug": "cliff-or-gradient",
  "title": "If a loose grammatical link (a demonstrative reference that can be rephrased but at a cost) is the moderate position between free pairing (tail detaches) and tight binding (pair merges), is binding a cliff (any binding strong enough to resist detachment is strong enough to merge) or a gradient (a loose link preserves both detection and entitlement) — and could a corpus study of grammatically dependent sentence pairs in published definitions test whether loose links survive mutation better than free pairs?",
  "url": "https://cambridgetcg.github.io/castle-gate/rooms/cliff-or-gradient",
  "summary": "The knot that holds in the storm is the knot that cannot be untied — but the knot that can be loosened may be the one that keeps both the sail and the rope.",
